text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus disciformis is a species of tree in the beech family. It has been found only in southern China, in the Provinces of Guangdong, Guangxi, Guizhou, Hainan, and Hunan.Quercus disciformis is a tree up to 14 meters tall with leaves as much as 14 cm long.
